<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">June 10, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Standardized editorial bylines across the <a href="/articles" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/articles</a> back catalog to avoid implying a subject-matter-expert review that did not happen. Convention going forward: visible byline reads <em>&ldquo;BreederHQ Editorial &middot; Updated &lt;Month Year&gt;&rdquo;</em>, and the BlogPosting JSON-LD author is name-only (no jobTitle carrying freshness or review language). &ldquo;Reviewed&rdquo; language is reserved for content with a real named reviewer or a documented review process.</p>

  <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
    <p><strong>Changed (21 files):</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li>17 editorial guides: visible byline &ldquo;Last Reviewed May 2026&rdquo; &rarr; &ldquo;Updated May 2026&rdquo;; removed the <code>author.role</code> freshness/label string from BlogPosting JSON-LD (now name-only).</li>
      <li>2 puppy buyer/legal articles (health- and legal-sensitive): converted the full &ldquo;reviewed&rdquo; freshness system to &ldquo;updated&rdquo; consistently (byline, top stamp, bottom legal stamp, and the body self-references), preserving the legal substance (date stamp plus &ldquo;statutes change, re-verify&rdquo;). Author JSON-LD is name-only.</li>
      <li>pyometra reproductive-health article: byline + index card &rarr; &ldquo;Updated June 2026&rdquo; for full uniformity, name-only JSON-LD author. The &ldquo;informed by veterinary literature&rdquo; sourcing signal is retained in the article&rsquo;s body disclaimer (stronger placement for a health piece than a byline).</li>
      <li>Articles index: 19 card <code>role</code> labels &rarr; &ldquo;Updated &lt;Month&gt;&rdquo;.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Deliberately untouched:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li>Founder post (Aaron Payne &middot; &ldquo;Founder, BreederHQ&rdquo;): a real named author with a real role.</li>
      <li>Legitimate non-byline uses of &ldquo;reviewed&rdquo; in body copy (e.g. &ldquo;Application reviewed and accepted&rdquo;, &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve reviewed your responses&rdquo;).</li>
      <li>Internal <code>lastReviewedISO</code> variable names and code comments (not user-visible).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Verified in the production build: zero visible &ldquo;Last Reviewed&rdquo; strings remain across rendered articles; the only JSON-LD <code>jobTitle</code> values left are the two Organization founders and the founder post&rsquo;s named author. Build green.</p>
  </div>
</article>
